{{Infobox holiday |holiday_name = '''School Day of Non-violence and Peace (DENIP)''' |type = Observance |image = Logo_denip.jpg |imagesize = |caption = '''Logo DENIP''', by the painter ''[[Eulogio Díaz del Corral]]'' |official_name = |nickname = |observedby = |litcolor = |longtype = |significance = |begins = |ends = |date = |scheduling = <!-- e.g. "same day each year" --> |duration = <!-- e.g. "1 day", "1 week" --> |frequency = <!-- e.g. "annual", "every 4 years", "once" --> <!-- Use next three if holiday is the same day of the same week every year --> |week_ordinal = <!-- "first", "second", "last", etc. --> |weekday = <!-- "Sunday", "Monday", "Friday", etc. --> |month = <!-- "January", "February", "December", etc. --> <!-- Use next three if the date changes in an unusual pattern each year --> |date2013 = <!-- only for days that change each year --> |date2014 = <!-- only for days that change each year --> |date2015 = <!-- only for days that change each year --> |date2016 = <!-- only for days that change each year --> |celebrations = |observances = |relatedto = }}
The '''School Day of Non-violence and Peace''' (or '''DENIP''', acronym from [[Catalan language|Catalan]]-[[balearic dialect|Balearic]]: ''Dia Escolar de la No-violència i la Pau''), is an observance founded by the [[Spanish people|Spanish]] poet ''[[Llorenç Vidal Vidal]]'' in [[Majorca]] in 1964 as a starting point and support for a pacifying and [[non-violence|non-violent]] education of a permanent character.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nodo50.org/tortuga/Dia-Escolar-por-la-Noviolencia-y |title=Día Escolar por la Noviolencia y la Paz: ¿De qué va eso? |accessdate=2009-01-17 |format= |work=nodo50.org }}</ref> Different as the first proposed by the UNESCO "Armistice Day" in 1948,<ref name="cartadelapaz">{{cite web |url=http://www.cartadelapaz.org/portal_cp/anoticies_detall.php?id=682 |title=School Day Of Non-Violence And Peace |author=Unattributed |date=30 January 2009 |work=Letter of Peace addressed to the UN |publisher=cartadelapaz.org |accessdate=9 January 2012}}</ref> the "School Day of Non-violence and Peace" (DENIP) is observed on January 30 or thereabouts every year, on the anniversary of the death of [[Mahatma Gandhi]], in schools all over the world.<ref name="DENIP">{{cite web |url=http://denip.webcindario.com/denip.english.html |title=DENIP: School Day of Non-violence and Peace |author=Eulogio Díaz del Corral |work=DENIP |publisher= |accessdate=30 January 2012|type=or: [http://translate.google.co.in/translate?hl=en&sl=auto&tl=en&u=http%3A%2F%2Fdenip.webcindario.com%2F translate]}} English translation by the "Majorca Daily Bulletin" (Majorca). </ref> In countries with a Southern Hemisphere school calendar, it can be observed on 30 March.<ref name="DENIP"/> Its basic and permanent message is: ''"Universal love, [[non-violence]] and peace. Universal love is better than [[egotism|egoism]], non-violence is better than violence, and peace is better than war"''.<ref>[http://www.diariosur.es/20080130/gibraltar/tren-recorrera-localidad-escolar-20080130.html (Spanish) El Tren de la Paz recorrerá la localidad en el Día Escolar de la no Violencia. ''Sur.es''. Retrieved on 2009-01-17]</ref> In Navarra the slogan for the 2009 was "above all, we are friends" (Spanish:"''Por encima de todo, somos amigos''").<ref>[http://www.diariodenavarra.es/20080131/otrascomarcas/amigos-plaza-navarra.html?not=2008013103045683&dia=20080131&seccion=otrascomarcas&seccion2=otrascomarcas&chnl=10 (Spanish) Amigos en la plaza de Navarra. ''Diario de Navarra''. Retrieved on 2009-01-17]</ref> DENIP and World Association of Early Childhood Educators (AMEI-WAECE) collaborate to celebrate this event in the schools of the latter worldwide.<ref>[http://www.waece.org/webdenip2010/denip2010.htm#6 DENIP and World Association of Early Childhood Educators (AMEI-WAECE)]</ref> Former Director-General of [[UNESCO]], [[Federico Mayor Zaragoza]], has been promoting during decades the School Day of Non-violence and Peace, saying in [[Global Education Magazine]]: "We can not achieve a [[sustainable development]] without a culture of peace<ref>[http://www.globaleducationmagazine.com/dia-escolar-de-la-violencia-la-paz-entrevista-al-sr-federico-mayor-zaragoza/ Interview with Federico Mayor Zaragoza], [http://www.globaleducationmagazine.com/about-the-megazine/ Global Education Magazine]</ref>".
